  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/603739637" />
    <a title="Debra " class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/5032725-debra"><img alt="Debra " src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1627589236p2/5032725.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/603739637?book_show_action=true">Apr 30, 2013</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Debra " class="user" itemprop="url" name="Debra " href="/user/show/5032725-debra">Debra </a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/5032725-debra?shelf=first-reads-won">first-reads-won</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer603739637" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer9327784946745566102">**Received from Goodreads first reads giveaway.<br/><br/>This was a great psychological book. It is the story of a 20 year common law marriage (and both parties) falling apart. We witness the disintegration of their relationship through both Jodi and Todd&apos;s point of view. We see how they rationalize, excuse, cope and justify their behavior. Todd is a habitual cheater and Jodi is aware but never confronts him on it but always lets him know that she will be there for him waiting with elegant meals and pleas</span>
  <span id="freeText9327784946745566102" style="display:none">**Received from Goodreads first reads giveaway.<br /><br />This was a great psychological book. It is the story of a 20 year common law marriage (and both parties) falling apart. We witness the disintegration of their relationship through both Jodi and Todd's point of view. We see how they rationalize, excuse, cope and justify their behavior. Todd is a habitual cheater and Jodi is aware but never confronts him on it but always lets him know that she will be there for him waiting with elegant meals and pleasant conversation. Denial is what holds them together. Both seem to be fine with this arrangement until he gets the daughter of his best friend pregnant. This is where the unraveling really begins.<br /><br />This book was great. Even though I have mentioned the plot there is more much more. Subtle nuances, subtleties that really make this book work, some twists, turns and well....read it for yourself. I highly recommend this book.</span>
  <a data-text-id="9327784946745566102" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

