  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1468241005" />
    <a title="Kala" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/14480082-kala"><img alt="Kala" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1619708298p2/14480082.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1468241005?book_show_action=true">Nov 27, 2017</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Kala" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Kala" href="/user/show/14480082-kala">Kala</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="did not like it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">did not like it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/14480082-kala?shelf=boring">boring</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1468241005" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer1392988368433157517"><br/>I don&apos;t mind a book that&apos;s a slow burn. The Girls by Emma Cline was one of my favorites because I found the characters fascinating. But The Silent Wife just wasn&apos;t interesting enough to keep ME interested. Jodi was so bland and naive! It was hard for me to feel sorry for her. Neither she nor Todd had any sort of personality or chemistry. I&apos;m fine with the blurb giving away the ending, I just wanted to go along for the ride to see how it came to that ending. But the ride was slow and a major disa</span>
  <span id="freeText1392988368433157517" style="display:none"><br />I don't mind a book that's a slow burn. The Girls by Emma Cline was one of my favorites because I found the characters fascinating. But The Silent Wife just wasn't interesting enough to keep ME interested. Jodi was so bland and naive! It was hard for me to feel sorry for her. Neither she nor Todd had any sort of personality or chemistry. I'm fine with the blurb giving away the ending, I just wanted to go along for the ride to see how it came to that ending. But the ride was slow and a major disappointment. There were alot of unanswered questions and a few side plots that led to nowhere. Comparing it to Gone Girl is a huge insult.</span>
  <a data-text-id="1392988368433157517" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

