        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3762851036" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer9722754907381797404">I honestly think this is a well written novel. It&apos;s just mismarketed giving the readers wrong expectations and thus the general low average on Goodreads. It&apos;s like every single book about vile, cheating men who can be so stupid that their wives would set them up to their doom will be compared to &apos;Gone Girl&apos; but &apos;The Silent Wife&apos; isn&apos;t like it at all.<br/><br/>I feel like this novel would have fared better to readers had it been advertised as a literary fiction because it reads like it. I probably would ha</span>
  <span id="freeText9722754907381797404" style="display:none">I honestly think this is a well written novel. It's just mismarketed giving the readers wrong expectations and thus the general low average on Goodreads. It's like every single book about vile, cheating men who can be so stupid that their wives would set them up to their doom will be compared to 'Gone Girl' but 'The Silent Wife' isn't like it at all.<br /><br />I feel like this novel would have fared better to readers had it been advertised as a literary fiction because it reads like it. I probably would have rated it better if I hadn't plunged into it expecting a thrilling read. <br /><br />It's beautifully written although a little slow for my taste, with keen attention with the minutiae common to literary fics. The characters are flawed and unlikable, like in most satirical novels but they're quite believable and convincing. Even the ending gives poetic justice to the story.<br /><br />I would have read the other novels written by the author, unfortunately she passed away a year after she published her debut fiction. *Sniffs*.<br /></span>
  <a data-text-id="9722754907381797404" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


